I've seen one too many takes the last week defending Hamas as "freedom fighters".

Just so you're clear on this, the founding covenant of Hamas, the document that is the basis of their entire organization, calls for the extermination not only of Israel as a nation-state, but the actual deaths of all Jewish people worldwide, in order to bring about the End Times. That's not propaganda, that's literally what their own document says.

You cannot make peace with an organization whose foundational purpose is to murder you. I do not think Westerners understand that Hamas is actually serious about that whole "no Jews in Palestine because we killed all of them everywhere on Earth" idea.

Wanting a free, internationally recognized Palestine is reasonable -- I even agree with it.

But the number of LGBTQA+ people I've seen cheering on an organization which would literally rape and murder them and their families if given the chance sickens my queer ass to the bone.

Now, I could sit here for an hour and point out 100 things Israel did that they shouldn't do. Settlers pushing people out of their homes? Not fucking cool. Stop doing that shit. But you cannot be expected to make peace with a government which is out to kill you as its main reason for existing -- your options are fight or surrender. How to fight is open to debate -- I would make difference decisions, as would you.

Is there a queer/trans hacker or maker space in the San Francisco Bay Area that's transit accessible? That I might join?

The closest one to me is HackerMoms (North Oakland, CA) and I've donated tools to them before, but I'm not sure if I'm really the right fit (I'll go see this month or next at their open house). But I'm not a parent - but I do like to volunteer to help parents out. So I don't know.

SudoRoom (Temescal Neighborhood, Oakland, CA) seems like it may be a good fit, but I'm not entirely sure about it either. I've joined the mailing list and see if there's a good fit there too.

I would totally be willing to check out a transit accessible hacker/maker space in SF too, or other areas, as long as the transit is a reasonable journey for me.

FWIW, I am capable of doing stuff like woodwork and other forms of crafting, notably knife sharpening and origami, but my specialties are in script writing/programming in many languages, legacy and contemporary. I also am pretty skilled in data work (analytics and machine learning) - though I seem to be allergic to "AI". And I'm not at all interested in cryptocurrency, though I'm quite literate in cryptography/digital security.

no, Hamas have always been fucked up, they kill Palestinians who get in their way, they brainwash kids into stabbing random people and strapping bombs to their chests, they were supported by Mossad since way back in the day
